  <section id="haltepunkt">
  <bookmark branch="hid/.uno:ToggleBreakPoint" xml-lang="en-US" id="bm_id3159224"/><paragraph id="hd_id3154863" role="heading" level="1" oldref="1" l10n="U" xml-lang="en-US"><link href="text/sbasic/shared/02/11070000.xhp" name="Breakpoint">Breakpoint</link></paragraph>
  <paragraph l10n="U" role="paragraph" id="par_id3155364" xml-lang="en-US" oldref="2"><ahelp hid=".uno:ToggleBreakPoint" visibility="visible">Inserts a breakpoint in the program line.</ahelp></paragraph>
  </section>
  <paragraph xml-lang="en-US" oldref="4" role="paragraph" id="par_id3149346" l10n="U">The breakpoint is inserted at the cursor position. Use a breakpoint to interrupt a program just before an error occurs. You can then troubleshoot the program by running it in <link href="text/sbasic/shared/02/11050000.xhp" name="Single Step">Single Step</link> mode until the error occurs. You can also use the<link href="text/sbasic/shared/02/11080000.xhp" name="Watch">Watch</link> icon to check the content of the relevant variables.</paragraph>
